Dirty Girl is an obstacle course run for women of all ages and athletic abilities near Milwaukee. Don't worry - it's not a "race" in the traditional sense. It’s an untimed 5k mud run designed to push you slightly out of your comfort zone, but only as far as you want to go. Forming teams is encouraged, and so is helping your fellow Dirty Girls to the finish with some mud, sweat and cheers. At a Dirty Girl Mud Run you'll find excitement, laughter and camaraderie—as well as lots of music and even some adult beverages. It's a mud-covered day you'll never forget. 

We proudly support cancer survivors of all kind and offer 300 complimentary entries to each of our events. If you're a cancer survivor, send us a quick email that simply says "I'm a survivor!" along with which event you'd like to participate in to survivor@humanmovement.me to claim your free entry. 

 

Please Note: Human Movement has a no refund policy. Participants can transfer their registration to another person or another event within the calendar event year. Participants can not transfer to the next year. Along with our policy, if a venue is changed from the original advertised venue, and is still an hour and a half from the advertised city, a refund will not be given.

description:
Join us February 26 & 27 at Fifth Third Ballpark in Comstock Park, just north of Grand Rapids for the 11th annual Winter Beer Festival of the Michigan Brewers Guild. This popular event will feature near 100 Michigan breweries and over 800 craft beers, as well as local music, ice sculptures and carving demonstrations, fire pits to chase away the cold, and food available for purchase.

FAQs

Is this an outdoor event?

Yes! This festival takes place outdoors. In February. In Michigan. Please make wardrobe choices accordingly.

 

Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?

All festival attendees must be 21 or older to enter, even if they are designated drivers and are not drinking. A valid government ID is required for festival entry, with NO exceptions.

 

Where do I pick up my tokens?

You can pick up tokens from the token tent immediately after entering the festival.

 

Why do I need to use tokens if I already paid for a ticket?

The Michigan Brewers Guild utilizes drink tokens and specially marked cups to assure that we comply with Michigan Liquor Control Commission regulation and have a controlled means of serving beer. All festivals attendees are expected to willingly provide a token for each and every sample of beer received. Thank you for your cooperation which keeps us in compliance with state law.

 

What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?

Parking will be available at Fifth Third Ballpark. There will also be a shuttle (reservations required) running from several area hotels as well as downtown. More shuttle information will be posted to our website at www.mibeer.com/winter-festival as it becomes available - or visit Experience Grand Rapids for more details.

 

What can/can't I bring to the event?

The following items are not permitted on festival grounds: outside alcohol, glass containers, children, animals, bicycles, skateboards, or rollerskates/rollerblades.

You may bring any of the following items with you to the festival: water and other non-alcoholic beverages in non-glass containers, food, folding/camping chairs, coolers.

 

Is my registration/ticket transferrable? How do I transfer my ticket to another attendee?

Yes, tickets are transferrable - but each bar code will only scan one time. You do not need to do anything special to transfer your ticket to another attendee's name. Purchaser name will not be checked against ID-holder name at the gate.

 

Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?

You must bring a ticket with you to be scanned to allow you entry to the festival. This ticket can either be printed or be the electronic version accessible on your smartphone or wireless device.

 

How can I get early admission to the event?

Enthusiasts with valid membership ID card and VIPs with valid VIP pass will be permitted into the festival early (2pm Friday / noon Saturday), one hour prior to general admission. If you'd like to participate in early entry, you can sign up as an Enthusiast Member prior to the festival date.

 

What is the refund policy?

Tickets are non-refundable. The festival will occur rain (or snow) or shine.

 

Can I buy a Designated Driver ticket and then buy tokens for drinks if I change my mind?

No. Servers will not pour beer to Designated Drivers, and anyone caught drinking on a Designated Driver ticket will be immediately ejected from the festival.

 

Where can I find more information about the festival?

For the most current information, visit our website at www.mibeer.com/winter-festival.

Shuto Con is Lansing's Annual Anime Convention, coming to the Lansing Center and Radisson Hotel Lansing March 18th-20th, 2016. This convention will be a three day event held in Lansing, MI that focuses on Artists and the art of Interactive Cosplaying!

 

Starting Friday morning at the Lansing Center and Radisson Hotel Lansing our convention will run from 9AM until 6PM Sunday afternoon. We now have larger rooms for panels, over 50 unique artists, several dealers to get your latest anime goodies from, a large video game room open during the entire convention, table top gaming, special guests, and much more!

 

Shuto Con also hopes to give you a truly unique experience by participating in our “Interactive Cosplay” experience. We highly encourage ALL our attendees to dress up as their favorite characters and act like them during the convention. A mock battle arena will be staged where you can “fight” it out with other cosplayers, or even take “bets” on who will win (no real gambling is allowed at Shuto Con)! Special points will be given out to those that participate the most, and at Closing Ceremonies on Sunday afternoon we will announce the Shuto Con “King and Queen of Cosplayers”! If you do not wish to participate, but would still like to capture those fond memories, we ask that your bring your cameras and/or video recorders and witness a viral hit in the making! For more information and rules on this event please visit the Interactive Cosplay page.

 

Also, be sure to check out our Facebook and Twitter pages! Our Facebook page is updated almost daily with special events around Lansing, andis an excellent tool to use for planning your convention trip and meeting up with friends!

description:
Join us for a winery tour through Michigan wine country, complete with lunch and round-trip transportation. After a two-hour drive to Michigan wine country aboard a chartered bus, you'll hit four wineries: Lemon Creek Winery, Founders Wine Cellar, St. Julian Winery Tasting Room and Round Barn Winery Tasting Room. At each, you'll enjoy wine tastings (up to 20 in total) -- plus, at Founders Wine Cellar, a hearty lunch will be served.  You have your choice of chicken or roast pork, pasta, veggies, dessert, and bottled water.  Be sure to bring some extra cash, because discounted purchases of wine will be available throughout the day!

 

Schedules

BUS 1

8:45AM - Arrive and check-in at 640 N. Wells St.

9:00AM - Bus departs

11:00AM - Lemon Creek Winery

12:00PM - Founder's Winery

2:00PM - Round Barn and St. Julian Winery

3:30PM - Depart MI and head back to Chicago

5:00PM - Arrive back at 640 N. Wells St.

 

BUS 2

10:30AM - Arrive and check-in at 640 N. Wells St.

10:45AM - Bus departs

12:30PM - Lemon Creek Winery

1:30PM - Founder's Winery

3:30PM - Round Barn & St. Julian Winery

5:00PM - Depart MI and head back to Chicago

6:30PM - Arrive back at 640 N. Wells St.

 

*All times subject to change due to weather, traffic, or other factors beyond our control


FAQs 
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?
You must be 21+ to attend and valid photo ID is required as proof of age

What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?
Pick up location at 640 N. Wells is walking distance from a variety of CTA bus and train lines. Public parking located at Ohio and Franklin, Franklin and Erie, and Erie and Wells.

What can/can't I bring to the event?
Food and non-alcoholic beverages are permitted on the bus, no alcoholic beverages allowed on bus before our first winery. No glass and no coolers in the cabin but allowed to be stored under the bus. No pets. No one under the age of 21 years old will be permitted under any circumstances.

Are bathrooms available during the tour?
There are bathrooms on the bus and restrooms will be available at all winery stops. It is recommended to use the bus bathroom only as an emergency.

What do I do with personal belongings while at each winery?
We recommend carrying all valuables with you during the day. The bus will be locked or secured by a chauffeur at all times during the day should you choose to leave anything on the bus. All personal items are your responsibility.

Where can I contact the organizer with any questions?
hello@cannonballproductions.com

Is my registration/ticket transferrable?
Your ticket IS transferable to another individual 21+. To do this, please email your ticket to the person replacing you and have them check in under your reservation. No name change on the ticket/reservation is required.

Your ticket is NOT transferable to another date/time after 24 hours from purchase. No exceptions.

Is my purchase refundable?
We honor refund requests that are made within 24 hours of purchase. Refunds will not be given, under any circumstances, after the initial 24 hour purchase period. No full or partial refunds are given to customers who miss an event.

If an event is cancelled, purchasers will be notified prior to canceled or rescheduled tour. Canceled tours will be fully refunded. If you can't make the new date of a rescheduled tour, you are entitled to a refund upon request.

What's the cancellation policy?
If your tour is cancelled due to dangerous weather conditions or any other reason, you will be notified, with the email used to purchase your ticket, no later than 5pm CST the day before your scheduled tour.

As part of our efforts to help students start and grow companies, the Coleman Entrepreneurship Center will continue a series of Startup Advising Workshops (SAW) this year.

These workshops focus on addressing initial startup questions, and connecting students to the resources they need. The workshops are designed to be an important first step in working with the Center. 

Spring quarter workshops begin on Tuesday, January 12th, and will run on a rolling basis each month. The first workshop of each month will be Startup 101, a foundational program on launching a business. The second and third monthly workshop will rotate each month among topics such as Funding for Startups, Networking, Social Media and Marketing, Legal Basics, Intro to Chicago Startup Ecosystem, Building the Right Team, Accounting Basics, and Sales Basics for Startups. The workshop series will alternate days of the week each month in order to best accomodate class schedules and provide everyone the chance to attend.  

Startup Advising Workshops run for one hour, 3:30 pm to 4:30 pm, and are open to all members of the DePaul community, from across the university.
